The journal aims to create a platform for an<br>innovative interdisciplinary discourse in the field of communication<br>and media studies, with a focal point on pure communication inquiry. [...]    </description>   <dc:date>2015-02-14T17:06:56+01:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>Janos Toth</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=IAMS;60058e72.1502</dc:identifier> </item>  <item rdf:about="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=IAMS;719899d.1410">   <title>International Conference Beliefs and Behaviours in Education and Culture, Timisoara Romania </title>   <link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=IAMS;719899d.1410</link>   <description> Dear Colleagues,<br><br>The Teacher Training Department, West University of Timi\ufffd\ufffdoara (Romania), is<br>pleased to announce the International Conference *Beliefs and Behaviours in<br>Education and Culture*, which<br>will be held in June 25 - 27, 2015.<br><br>The aim of the conference, proposing interdisciplinary perspectives, is to<br>build comprehensive and holistic explanations of beliefs from different<br>sciences that have a great impact upon education and culture. The<br>conference addresses themes related to issues and processes of education at<br>any level, from kindergarten to lifelong learning, from formal to informal<br>education. [...]   </description>   <dc:date>2014-10-31T15:31:08+02:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>carmen tiru</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=IAMS;719899d.1410</dc:identifier> </item>  <item rdf:about="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=IAMS;e0fb8e8b.1410">   <title>Bullying Through Technology </title>   <link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=IAMS;e0fb8e8b.1410</link>   <description> Hi All,<br><br>This may be of interest to some on the IAMS list.<br><br>I'm a doctoral researcher at the University of Sheffield, investigating how negative behaviours received through technology affect employees. To understand the impact of negative technology perpetrated acts, I'm looking for volunteers to take a questionnaire involving questions on negative technological experiences, job satisfaction, health and work engagement.
